# SAFETY_POLICY.profile.md - csharp_desktop

## Purpose

Define C# desktop safety defaults.

## Side Effects

Desktop apps may write files, user settings, logs, caches, or local databases. Treat those as side effects unless documented as safe test artifacts.

## Machine-Specific Data

Do not commit:
- User-specific absolute paths.
- Local machine identifiers.
- Credentials or tokens.
- Private documents or desktop data.

## Phase Gate

Do not modify source code before the current phase allows implementation. If the phase is inspection or planning, produce findings only.

## Verification Safety

Smoke procedures should use safe local test data and avoid changing real user data.
